                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-244-off1302 t18270531-244-victim1348"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>THOMAS BRIGHT. I am a <rs id="t18270531-244-viclabel1304" type="occupation">broker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-244-victim1348 t18270531-244-viclabel1304"></join>, and live in Queen's-<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182705310097"></xptr>place, Westminster. On the 24th of April I went to the <placeName id="t18270531-244-crimeloc1305">King's Head public-house, Orchard-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-244-crimeloc1305" type="placeName" value="King's Head public-house, Orchard-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-244-crimeloc1305" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-244-off1302 t18270531-244-crimeloc1305"></join>, and had a pint of beer and a pipe; I gave the prisoner, who was the waiter, a sovereign - I told him to take for a pint of beer and a pipe, which he had served me with, and bring me the change; this was between eight and nine o'clock in the evening; I did not see him again till the 30th (at Queen-square;) the landlord gave me the change afterwards, on condition of my prosecuting him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-244-person1349">
                  JOHN 
                  JAMES
               <interp inst="t18270531-244-person1349" type="surname" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-244-person1349" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-244-person1349" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep this house. The prisoner was an <rs id="t18270531-244-deflabel1306" type="occupation">occasional waiter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-244-defend1347 t18270531-244-deflabel1306"></join>; he was there on Tuesday, the 24th of April, in that capacity. Bright frequented the house; he called for a pint of beer that day, and gave the prisoner a sovereign - he left the house immediately, without his hat on; I saw him in custody on the Saturday following. It was his duty to bring me the sovereign to change; I gave Bright the change afterwards - I asked the prisoner about it- he said he took the sovereign, and bought some clothes with it - I have not received it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-244-person1350">
                  THOMAS 
                  SPEED
               <interp inst="t18270531-244-person1350" type="surname" value="SPEED"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-244-person1350" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-244-person1350" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. On the 24th Jones told me of this, and on the 28th I saw the prisoner at a shop window, and took him.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18270531-244-verdict1307" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270531-244-verdict1307" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
